 and Student Social, Emotional, Behavioral and Mental Health during COVID-19 Era</a> from the U.S. Department of Education.</p>    <p>Then tune in below...</p>      <button class="accordion"> Stress Relief Resources</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img name="" src="../images/stacked-stones-and-sand-circles.jpg" width="1000" height="317" alt="white stacked stones on white sand" /></p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://www.travelandleisure.com/attractions/museums-galleries/museums-with-virtual-tours?fbclid=IwAR2zyS1geqZBiyOqLqG5XAFaCIsL4H8iDqgezGWZVec6kZnvME0rJIb6Oc8" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.travelandleisure.com/attractions/museums-galleries/museums-with-virtual-tours?fbclid%3DIwAR2zyS1geqZBiyOqLqG5XAFaCIsL4H8iDqgezGWZVec6kZnvME0rJIb6Oc8&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707295000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFYf2-hZEKLMS5JYInCp2x1BAqX2Q">12 Famous Museums Offer Virtual Tours</a> - Google Arts &amp; Culture teamed up with over 2500 museums and galleries around the world to bring you virtual tours and online exhibits of some of the most famous museums around the world.</li>        <li><a href="http://cincinnatizoo.org/home-safari-resources/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://cincinnatizoo.org/home-safari-resources/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707295000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHy9T-JC7Pkogl6VhkIVATUOYU2Cw">Cincinnati Zoo's Home Safari Lessons </a>- A live engaging video lesson with an animal every weekday at 3PM ET. They take live questions toward the end, then there&rsquo;s a quiz!</li>        <li><a href="https://www.kennedy-center.org/education/mo-willems/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.kennedy-center.org/education/mo-willems/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707295000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHWV8eZoBqBaQutm6Km0n7la8oVYA">Lunch Doodles with Mo Williams</a> - Kennedy Center Education Artist-in-Residence at Home; New episodes will be posted each weekday at 1:00 p.m. ET and then remain online to be streamed afterwards.  Check back each weekday for new LUNCH DOODLES!</li>      </ul>      <p>(Additional stress-relief videos can be found at the end of this resource)</p>      <p>&nbsp;</p>    </div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h3>Now Let's Get Started Looking Through the Lens of MCH!</h3>    <button class="accordion"> Self-Reflection</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img name="" src="../images/old-time-light-bulb-and-crumpled-paper.jpg" width="1000" height="303" alt="old time lightbulb and crumpled paper" /></p>      <p>Being quarantined definitely lends itself to being able to reflect on ourselves and our families.  </p>      <p>The following resources support a time for solidarity and reflection during the COVID-19 pandemic:</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://www.mhe-sme.org/covid-19/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.mhe-sme.org/covid-19/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHgnlX1Yn7yQSVloXFdxg09tEHF6A">Eight Ways to Look After Your Mental Health During Covid-19 Pandemic</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/covid-19-how-to-isolate-at-home.html" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/covid-19-how-to-isolate-at-home.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNECY7im6Wd-yUl8uoLXLZ1_zV6xRw">How to isolate at home when you have COVID-19</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/self-monitoring-self-isolation-isolation-for-covid-19.html" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.canada.ca/en/public-health/services/publications/diseases-conditions/self-monitoring-self-isolation-isolation-for-covid-19.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFeCe7PuD4CAkOzGwrU5ZaCIqppxA">Know the Difference : Self-monitoring, self-isolation, and isolation for COVID-19</a></li>      </ul>      <p>&nbsp;</p>    </div>    <button class="accordion"> Ethics</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img src="../images/ethics-spelled-out-wood-blocks.jpg" width="1000" height="377" alt="Ethics spelled out in wooden blocks" /></p>      <p>The COVID-19 virus forces us to think ethically about our behaviors and best practices on staying safe.</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://www.thehastingscenter.org/ethics-resources-on-the-coronavirus/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.thehastingscenter.org/ethics-resources-on-the-coronavirus/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGoyVHRu1VPNOHsK7_EJ-PBKlxO2A">Ethics Resources on the Coronavirus (COVID-19)</a></li>        <li><a href="https://journalofethics.ama-assn.org/podcast/ethics-talk-covid-19-pandemic-response" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://journalofethics.ama-assn.org/podcast/ethics-talk-covid-19-pandemic-response&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGLvmf7THDh4tFx_nm_n-FLn1wmIQ">Ethics Talk: COVID-19 Pandemic Response - Podcast</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.nuffieldbioethics.org/news/responding-to-the-covid-19-pandemic-ethical-considerations" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.nuffieldbioethics.org/news/responding-to-the-covid-19-pandemic-ethical-considerations&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHak4Vh6zaSETf_Dl0xecMj7xHPpA">New briefing: Responding to the COVID-19 pandemic - ethical considerations</a></li>        <li><a href="https://medicine.iu.edu/blogs/bioethics/the-ethics-of-coronavirus" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://medicine.iu.edu/blogs/bioethics/the-ethics-of-coronavirus&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHEWO1Rp_FB8Ii3j2nh5uDJn-AAqg">The Ethics of Coronavirus</a></li>      </ul>    </div>    <button class="accordion"> Critical Thinking</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img src="../images/man-looking-up-at-multicolored-arrows.jpg" width="1000" height="324" alt="Man gazing up at colorful arrows going in many directions" /></p>      <p>The virus has sparked conversations about the history of pandemics in our society and forced us to understand as much as possible about how they occur and best practices for &quot;flattening the curve.&quot;</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/11/learning/coronavirus-resources-teaching-learning-and-thinking-critically.html" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/11/learning/coronavirus-resources-teaching-learning-and-thinking-critically.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGqQWmV7W3m03U-hfTK244cIezpGQ">Coronavirus Resources: Teaching, Learning and Thinking Critically</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.visier.com/clarity/covid-19-pandemic-ask-these-critical-workforce-questions/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.visier.com/clarity/covid-19-pandemic-ask-these-critical-workforce-questions/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHe6PdikM4pxQOEV2CR84PifZy4fA">COVID-19 Pandemic: Are You Asking These Critical Workforce Questions?</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.pbs.org/newshour/science/one-simple-chart-explains-how-social-distancing-saves-lives" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/science/one-simple-chart-explains-how-social-distancing-saves-lives&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFBdArKsKko7H1YeBWXVcL7O7DkrQ">Understanding and Thinking Critically About 'Flattening the Curve'</a></li>      </ul>    </div>    <button class="accordion"> Communication</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img src="../images/colorful-conversation-boxes-on-top-of-square-notes.jpg" width="1000" height="310" alt="Colorul conversation boxes on top of square notes pads" /></p>      <p>With news seemingly changing by the minute, this is definitely a time to think about how we are communicating information, especially among families with young children.</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://www.pbs.org/education/blog/how-to-talk-to-little-learners-about-coronavirus" target="_blank">How to Talk to Little Learners About COVID-19</a> – Having Hard Conversations is E.A.S.Y.</li>        <li><a href="https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/communication/index.html" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/communication/index.html&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNF734kzrzT6GfBmik9NU0DsPJ-UAQ">CDC's COVID-19 Communication Resources</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.johnahartford.org/dissemination-center/view/vitaltalk-resource-covid-19-communication-skills" target="_blank">VitalTalk Resource: COVID-19 Communication Skills</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.huffpost.com/entry/coronavirus-how-to-talk-to-kids-disease_l_5e5c615ac5b601022113151d">Coronavirus: How To Talk To Your Kids About The Disease</a></li>      </ul>    </div>    <button class="accordion"> Negotiation and Conflict Resolution</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img src="../images/2-hands-pulling-rope.jpg" width="1000" height="273" alt="two hands pulling at opposite ends of a short rope" /></p>      <p>Everyone may not agree on best practices to protect ourselves from the virus.  There may even be disagreement between individuals in the same living quarters.  This presents a moment to utilize our skills around negotiation and conflict resolution.</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://pollackpeacebuilding.com/blog/tips-to-prevent-workplace-conflict-during-covid-19-crisis/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://pollackpeacebuilding.com/blog/tips-to-prevent-workplace-conflict-during-covid-19-crisis/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNFm_tRhnQ_95RuzuSNKAyZHSHZ38w">Tips to Prevent Workplace Conflict During COVID-19 Crisis: Online Panel Discussion</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.mediate.com/articles/durazo-coronavirus-online.cfm" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.mediate.com/articles/durazo-coronavirus-online.cfm&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEf_3bMnwl-NVIG_R3m4Eg4eqJuhw">In an Era of Chaos with the Coronavirus; The Solution to Support our Leaders is Online Mediation</a></li>        <li><a href="https://progressiveconflictsolutions.com/got-coronavirus-conflict/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://progressiveconflictsolutions.com/got-coronavirus-conflict/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEgCQ5KOdPDj9K5nqt9UrSiMqs4Vw">Got Coronavirus Conflict?</a><a href="https://progressiveconflictsolutions.com/got-coronavirus-conflict/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://progressiveconflictsolutions.com/got-coronavirus-conflict/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEgCQ5KOdPDj9K5nqt9UrSiMqs4Vw"> - Progressive Conflict Solutions</a></li>      </ul>    </div>    <button class="accordion"> Family-Professional Partnerships</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img src="../images/row-of-colorful-rubber-boots.jpg" width="1000" height="357" alt="Row of colorful rubber boots" /></p>      <p>We are encouraged during this time to communicate with our health professionals if we have symptoms and depend on their expertise and advice on how to proceed.</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://eiclearinghouse.org/resources/trying-times/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://eiclearinghouse.org/resources/trying-times/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHcKau1pFWSfJORvuxVKug_ef33Pg">Everyday Early Intervention During Coronavirus</a></li>        <li><a href="https://www.newsobserver.com/news/coronavirus/article241262911.html" target="_blank">Tips for families as coronavirus spreads</a></li>        <li><a href="https://hbr.org/2020/03/how-working-parents-can-prepare-for-coronavirus-closures" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://hbr.org/2020/03/how-working-parents-can-prepare-for-coronavirus-closures&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707296000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGK5lAAcy5mbX_82UeO4tAqQi82AQ">How Working Parents Can Prepare for Coronavirus Closures</a></li>      </ul>    </div>    <button class="accordion"> Cultural Competency</button>    <div class="panel">      <p><img src="../images/flags-of-many-counties-on-flagpoles.jpg" width="1000" height="274" alt="Flags of many countries flying on flagpoles" /></p>      <p>The virus has forced us to have a worldly point of view as it relates to the spread of disease across the globe. We must be respectful of culture and personal practices during this time and use it as an opportunity for learning.</p>      <ul>        <li><a href="https://www.healthequityinitiative.org/covid-19-and-health-equity-resources.html">COVID-19 and Health Equity Resources</a> (Health Equity Initiative)</li>        <li><a href="https://www.ama-assn.org/delivering-care/health-equity/covid-19-health-equity-resources">COVID-19 Health Equity Resources</a> (American Medical Association)</li>        <li><a href="https://www.naacp.org/coronavirus/" target="_blank" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.naacp.org/coronavirus/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1585229707297000&amp;usg=AFQjCNG0uOCcNaiTGKin2Fzty6EsegQtEQ">Coronavirus and our Communities</a></li>        <li><a href=